entry.title: Hippocrates
entry.subtitle: 460 - 370 BCE
entry.short: Hippocrates of Kos, also known as Hippocrates II, was a Greek physician of the Age of Pericles (Classical Greece), who is considered one of the most outstanding figures in the history of medicine.
